%N A397375 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (zeta(2) - H(k,2))*H(k)/(2*k+1), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, and H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 2.
%H A397375 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.29, p. 431, eq. (4.120), section 5.29, p. 463, section 6.29, pp. 646-651.
%H A397375 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A397375 Equals log(2)^4/6 - log(2)^2*zeta(2) - zeta(4)/2 + 4*Li_4(1/2).
%e A397375 0.776913616156587749440029749938859188817810502311313...
%t A397375 RealDigits[Log[2]^4/6 - Log[2]^2*Zeta[2] - Zeta[4]/2 + 4*PolyLog[4, 1/2], 10, 120][[1]]
